<Class name="CMIF_MenuParams" id="3b369d52-2c6c-4885-a28e-3f2bd5308fb1">
    <superclass name="CMIF_Object"/>
    <transient/>
    <persistentAllowed/>
    <sharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassPersistentAllowed/>
    <subclassSharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassTransientAllowed/>
    <transientAllowed/>
    <text>MenuItems have an attribute UserObject.

This is good because it allows you to set the object that the menuitem is refering to at the tme that you set the caption etc.

However some times you may want to have several objects or strings etc. that is what this is for.</text>
    <DbClassMap file="userData"/>
